OL,6,FEveryone seems to be putting this down
OL,7,Fto a rush in the UK to get the
OL,8,Flegislation passed rather than any
OL,9,Fcynical plan to infringe upon the
OL,10,Frights of the Crown Dependencies.
OL,12,FBut so often we hear of
OL,13,Fmisunderstanding in Westminster about
OL,14,Fthe powers of those running the show
OL,15,Fhere.
OL,17,FThis is another example perhaps of the
OL,18,FCrown Dependencies being an
OL,19,Fafterthought in the British
OL,20,FParliament's halls of power.
